`rc-field-form` is a React library that provides a simple and efficient way to handle form validation and submission. The library provides a set of components to build complex forms and integrates well with other libraries such as `antd` and `formik`.

Here's an example of how to use `rc-field-form` with `useForm` hook:
```javascript
import React from 'react';
import { Form, Input, Button } from 'antd';
import { useForm } from 'rc-field-form';

const DemoForm = () => {
  const [form] = useForm();

  const handleSubmit = (values) => {
    console.log(values);
  };

  return (
    <Form
      form={form}
      onFinish={handleSubmit}
    >
      <Form.Item
        label="Username"
        name="username"
        rules={[{ required: true, message: 'Please input your username!' }]}
      >
        <Input />
      </Form.Item>

      <Form.Item
        label="Password"
        name="password"
        rules={[{ required: true, message: 'Please input your password!' }]}
      >
        <Input.Password />
      </Form.Item>

      <Form.Item>
        <Button type="primary" htmlType="submit">
          Submit
        </Button>
      </Form.Item>
    </Form>
  );
};

export default DemoForm;
```
In this example, we import the `useForm` hook from `rc-field-form`. We create a form using the `Form` component from `antd` and pass the `form` object returned by `useForm` as a prop. We also define an `onFinish` function to handle form submission.

Inside the form, we define two `Form.Item` components for `username` and `password` inputs. We set validation rules using the `rules` prop. Finally, we define a `Button` component to submit the form.

When the user submits the form, the `handleSubmit` function is called with the form values as an object. In this example, we simply log the values to the console.
